snippet.textDisplay: Most people use the wet food as a topper on the dry food. But in all honesty it sounds like she just likes the wet food, which fine to give her on it's own, just don't give her the whole can. Also another trick you can do is use salmon oil by the brand Wild Alaska and put two pumps on her food. It will help her skin and hair be more shiny and majority of cats love it as a topper on their solid dry food. I recently did that to my cat and she loves it. I have 4 cats and can tell you they all like wet and dry food, I also work at a pet store, and most of the costumers love to use the salmon oil on the food they have for dogs as well.

snippet.textDisplay:
It's usually vet recommended that cats have both wet and dry food.
My cat has dry food for 'breakfast' and then wet food for 'dinner'. I find she decides to eat her 'breakfast' gradually throughout the day which is completely natural. Cats are usually grazers. She eats her 'dinner' in one go. I always keep them separate, but it's what you feel works for your cat 😁 Trial and error, see what she likes best 😇 She is a very lucky and happy kitty 😍😍😍
